      <gap reason="omitted"/>
      <ab><milestone unit="section" n="Closing verses (45b4)"/>
        <lg><l><lb n="45b4"/> <rs type="work" ana="corpusmd:named_reference" ref="db:3729">bden gnyis rnam bshad</rs> <rs type="work" ana="corpusmd:named_reference" ref="db:6193">ti ka dag</rs> dang bcas ||</l> 
         <l>dam pa'i legs gsungs rang gi rtogs pa rnams || </l>
         <l>don rnam mang phyir gsal bar rjod pa'i phyir || </l>
         <l>gzhung mangs gyur kyang don gnyer rnams la phan || </l></lg>
         <lg><l>phyogs 'dir rab dad ye shes gis bskul || </l>
         <l>nus pa med kyang 'bad pas <rs type="work">gzhung</rs> 'di' sbyar ||<anchor xml:id="a82"/> </l>
         <l>de' ni 'gro rnams las 'dir myur zhags te || </l>
         <l>bla med byang chub grags pa<note type="editorial">Hidden signature "Byang chub grags," like in the closing verses of his dBu ma'i de kho na nyid gtan la dbab pa (ID:4686). This echoes the hidden signature "ye shes snying po"=Jñānagarbha (ID:3730) in the last verse of the Satyadvayavibhaṅgavṛtti (ID:3729).</note> skyed par shog ||</l></lg>
         <note type="editorial">The last two lines echo the closing verse of his commentary on the Bodhicaryāvatāra, work (ID:4478). See (ID:4477), fol. 83b3-83b4: bdag gis brjod par ma nus ste || slob ma dag [gis?] bskul phyir sbyar</note></ab>
      <gap reason="omitted"/>
